 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Online Retail Purchase\n",
    "\n",
    "Click the button below to run this notebook directly on Google Colab:\n",
    "\n",
    "[<img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" align=\"left\">](https://colab.research.google.com/github)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Introduction:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Step 1. Import the necessary libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 2. Import the dataset from this [address](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/Online_Retail.csv)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 3. Assign it to a variable called online_rt\n",
    "##### Note: if you receive an error about encoding, use `encoding = 'Latin1'` in `pd.read_csv()`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thieu1995/csv-files/main/data/pandas/Online_Retail.csv'\n",
    "online_rt = pd.read_csv(url, encoding='Latin1')\n",
    "online_rt.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 4. Create a histogram with the 10 countries that have the most 'Quantity' ordered except UK"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "countries = online_rt.groupby('Country').sum(numeric_only=True)\n",
    "countries = countries.sort_values(by='Quantity', ascending=False)[1:11]\n",
    "\n",
    "countries['Quantity'].plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Countries')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Quantity')\n",
    "plt.title('10 Countries with most Orders (Excluding UK)')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 5.  Exclude negative Quantity entries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "online_rt = online_rt[online_rt.Quantity > 0]\n",
    "online_rt.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 6. Create a scatterplot with the Quantity per UnitPrice by CustomerID for the top 3 countries; Netherlands, EIRE, Germany"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "customers = online_rt.groupby(['CustomerID', 'Country']).sum(numeric_only=True).reset_index()\n",
    "top_countries = ['Netherlands', 'EIRE', 'Germany']\n",
    "customers = customers[customers.Country.isin(top_countries)]\n",
    "\n",
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(customers, col='Country')\n",
    "g.map(plt.scatter, 'UnitPrice', 'Quantity', alpha=1)\n",
    "g.add_legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 7. Investigate why the previous results look so strange."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Step 7.1 For the EIRE customer, what are the item values with a negative Quantity, or Quantity equals 0?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# All negative and zero quantities were already filtered out in Step 5.\n",
    "# Let's inspect the data to understand the scaling better.\n",
    "customers.groupby('Country').UnitPrice.max()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Step 7.2 Change the scale of the x-axis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The layout becomes better when looking at the average rather than sum\n",
    "print('Investigating scaling and outliers across the targeted groups.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 8. Plot the total revenue per country, excluding the UK, over time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 8.1 Group the data by Country and find the total Revenue"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "online_rt['Revenue'] = online_rt['Quantity'] * online_rt['UnitPrice']\n",
    "revenue_per_country = online_rt[online_rt.Country != 'United Kingdom'].groupby('Country').Revenue.sum().reset_index()\n",
    "revenue_per_country.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 8.2 Get the top 5 countries by Revenue"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top5_revenue_countries = revenue_per_country.sort_values(by='Revenue', ascending=False).head(5)['Country'].tolist()\n",
    "top5_revenue_countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 8.3 Plot."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plot_data = online_rt[online_rt.Country.isin(top5_revenue_countries)]\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Country', y='Revenue', data=plot_data, estimator=sum, errorbar=None)\n",
    "plt.title('Total Revenue for Top 5 Non-UK Countries')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 8.4 Make it look nicer.\n",
    "x-axis needs values.  \n",
    "y-axis isn't that easy to read; show in terms of millions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Country', y='Revenue', data=plot_data, estimator=sum, errorbar=None, ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as ticker\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda y, pos: f'{y*1e-6:.1f}M'))\n",
    "plt.title('Total Revenue for Top 5 Non-UK Countries (In Millions)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Revenue (Millions)')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### BONUS: Create your own question and answer it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Question: What are the top 5 most sold products (by description) based on total Quantity?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,\n    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }\n   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "top_products = online_rt.groupby('Description').Quantity.sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5)\n",
    "top_products.plot(kind='barh')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 5 Most Sold Products by Quantity')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Total Quantity Sold')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Product Description')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
